C -*- Fortran -*-
C! Custom function `halt', used to work around to bugs in 
C! ther `stop' Fortran builtin as provided by some compilers
C! (e.g. gfortran 4.0, whose `stop' always produce a message
C! on stderr, even if used without arguments).
      subroutine halt
C       set at configure time
        @RAT4_FORTRAN_STOP@
      end
C vim: ft=fortran ts=4 sw=4 et
